<FIRST>r i PM-Colombia-Terrorism     12-07 0449</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Colombia-Terrorism,0463</SECOND>
<HEAD>Major Terrorist Violence in Colombia Since August</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Colombia, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Major terrorist attacks, including
bombings and assassinations, since the government's offensive
against drug traffickers began Aug. 18:
   Aug. 25 _ Bombs explode at Liberal and Conservative Party
offices in Medellin, and terrorists burn the country homes of a
former finance minister and a senator. One person dies in the
attack on the Liberal Party office. Police deactivate bombs placed
at the Medellin offices of two radio networks.
   Sept. 2 _ A car bomb explodes at a gas station beside the Bogota
offices of El Espectador newspaper, injuring two people.
   Sept. 25 _ A bomb explodes in the sixth floor of the Hilton
Hotel in Cartagena, killing two doctors attending a conference and
injuring five people.
   Sept. 27 _ A car bomb explodes at a gas station in Suba, less
than 15 miles northwest of Bogota, killing two people and injuring
five.
   Sept. 28 _ About 60 cars are damaged as a car bomb explodes in
the parking lot of the Tequendama Hotel in Bogota.
   Oct. 16 _ Four people die and nine are injured when a car bomb
explodes at the Vanguardia Liberal newspaper offices in the city of
Bucaramanga. About 80 percent of the building is destroyed and
nearby stores are damaged. The Extraditables, a group linked to the
Medellin cartel, claims responsibility for the attack on the paper.
   Oct. 17 _ Gunmen kill a federal judge, Hector Jimenez Rodriguez,
in front of his Medellin home. The Extraditables claim
responsibility.
   Oct. 18 _ A hand grenade carried by a terrorist explodes
accidentally in Bogota's main plaza, killing the man and injuring
four people. The terrorist had tried to enter the Congress but was
stopped by security guards.
   Oct. 20 _ The Royal Hotel in the city of Barranquilla is
targeted in a car bomb attack that injures six people.
   Oct. 24 _ Five police officers are killed and 16 injured when
terrorists set off a bomb beside a bus carrying officers to their
posts in Medellin.
   Nov. 2 _ A car bomb explodes under a Bogota bridge, killing four
people and injuring two.
   Nov. 27 _ An Avianca Airlines Boeing 727 crashes shortly after
takeoff from Bogota, killing all 107 people aboard. Government
investigators later say a bomb aboard the plane caused the crash.
   Dec. 5 _ Gunmen assassinate another judge, Bernardo Jaramillo,
in Medellin. The judge was handling several murder cases in which
drug traffickers were the principal suspects.
   Dec. 6 _ A truck bomb packing hundreds of pounds of dynamite
explodes in front of the offices of Colombia's federal
investigative police, killing at least 40 people. Hundreds are
injured.
</TEXT>
