<HEAD>Police Jail Man Accused of Threatening Johnny Carson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who police say has threatened
``Tonight Show'' host Johnny Carson for more than two years was
arrested in the lobby of the KNBC-TV studios where the program is
videotaped.
   Ken Orville Gause, 36, of Milwaukee was booked Wednesday for
investigation of making terrorist threats, attempted extortion and
carrying a concealed weapon, police Sgt. Don Goldberg said. He was
scheduled for arraignment Friday.
   Studio security guards notified police when Gause showed up at
the huge NBC complex and began ``making demands and threats,''
Goldberg said.
   He was carrying a ``slug,'' a sock weighted with a heavy
granular substance, when he was arrested, Goldberg said.
   Gause never got close to the talk-show host, Goldberg said.
   He had been under investigation for two years following threats
allegedly made against Carson in letters and tape-recorded messages
that also named other celebrities, detectives said.
   Carson spokesman Charlie Barrett declined to comment, and police
would not disclose which other celebrities were threatened.
