<HEAD>50 Killed When Bus Knocked Into River</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An overcrowded bus was knocked off a
narrow bridge into a river, killing at least 50 people, newspapers
reported Thursday.
   The bus driver was trying to get around a stalled car on the
bridge at Majidun, near Lagos, when the bus was struck from behind
by a truck and knocked into the river.
   The newspapers said the bus was supposed to carry 40 passengers
but was believed to have been carrying twice that number.
   No other details were immediately available.
