<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Hughes     12-07 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Hughes,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Grenadian Journalist Dies After Short Illness</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. GEORGE'S, Grenada (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cynthia Hughes, co-editor and
publisher of The Grenada Newsletter, has died at the age of 72.
   Mrs. Hughes fell ill Monday and died Wednesday at General
Hospital, said her husband, Alister.
   Together, they published the newsletter, a monthly publication
distributed in Grenada and mailed to subscribers around the world.
   They also were instrumental in getting news out to the world
during the military overthrow of the Maurice Bishop government in
1983, which resulted in the U.S.-led invasion of the tiny Caribbean
island.
   Funeral services will be held Saturday at the St. George's
Anglican Church. In addition to her husband, Mrs. Hughes is
survived by two daughters and a son.
</TEXT>
