<FIRST>r w AM-CubanPrisoner     12-07 0136</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Cuban Prisoner,130</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Official Says Cuban Prisoner Near Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A long-term Cuban political prisoner was near
death Thursday following 30 days on a hunger strike, a senior State
Department official said.
   Alfredo Mustelier, who was being fed intravenously against his
will in a Cuban military hospital, was ``close to death,'' said
Richard Schifter, assistant secretary of state for human rights.
``He clearly poses no threat to the Cuban government and has
already served a long and harsh sentence,'' Schifter said.
   Schifter, in a speech commemmorating the 41st anniversary of
United Nations adoption of the Universal Declaration of Human
Rights, repeated U.S. urgings that Mustelier be released
immediately on humanitarian grounds, along with two others who have
served more than 20 years in prison, Ernesto Diaz Rodriguez and
Mario Chanes de Armes.
</TEXT>
