<TEXT>
   City Olympics. July 11, age 49.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>ARNOLD LOBEL@ _ Prize-winning author and illustrator of</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   children's books. Dec. 4, age 54.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>1988</NOTE>
<NOTE>DAN BRADLEY@ _ Longtime advocate of the poor and disadvantaged</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   and former national president of Legal Services, federally funded
legal agency for the poor. Jan. 8, age 47.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>JOHN HOLMES@ _ Pornographic actor ``Johnny Wadd'' who made</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   hundreds of sexually explicit films. March 13, age 43.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>ARNIE ZANE@ _ Critically acclaimed, award-winning choreographer</NOTE>
<TEXT>
   who, with his partner Bill T. Jones, founded one of America's
leading post-modernist dance troupes. March 30, age 39.
</TEXT>
