<HEAD>Canadian Company Recalls Heaters Sold in U.S.</HEAD>
<UNK>Eds: The telephone number for Micromar in the last graf is 1-800-387-8971.</UNK>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Canadian manufacturer is recalling all
models in one line of electric portable heaters to correct a
potential fire hazard, the Consumer Product Safety Commission said.
   The company ``found that a potentially defective component had
been used in the heaters which could possibly cause a fire,'' the
agency said in a statement Wednesday.
   The recall involves ceramic heaters, sold nationwide in the
United States since September by Micromar Manufacturing Corp. of
London, Ontario, as Heat Machine 2000, model numbers HMG2000tc or
HMG2000vhc.
   ``We are very much committed to providing safe, effective
heaters to the public,'' said Paul McCann, a company spokesman. He
declined to say how many heaters were recalled.
   Consumers should immediately stop using the heaters and unplug
them, the commission said. They may call Micromar for directions on
returning the heaters for free repair.
