<TEXT>
   Martin Marietta Corp. on Thursday elected
A. Thomas Young, the company's executive vice president, to the
post of president and chief operating officer.
   Young, 51, succeeds Caleb B. Hurtt, who had announced he would
retire on Jan. 1.
