interest rates could be revived if Friday's monthly report from the
Labor Department on the employment situation provides evidence that
economic growth remains sluggish.
   But traders seemed reluctant to hold positions exposing them to
any surprises in the figures.
   Advance estimates on Wall Street call for the November data to
show an increase of about 150,000 in nonfarm payroll employment.
   Pinnacle West led the active list and jumped 4{ to 9~. The
company agreed to provide $450 million in cash and securities to
its Merabank savings and loan subsidiary, meeting a condition of an
offer for Pinnacle West made last week by Pacificorp.
   Chevron fell 5] to 66| and Pennzoil was down { at 82[. Pennzoil
said it had acquired 8.8 percent of Chevron's stock and might buy
more, but had no present plans for a takeover bid.
   Inland Steel, which lowered its fourth-quarter earnings
projection late Wednesday, lost 2~ to 31].
