<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
216,437 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
208,977, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 263,042 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
